Query to try and find duplicate filesets in the last week:

```sql
select a.id, b.id from orm_resources a, jsonb_array_elements(a.metadata->'file_metadata') AS file_metadata, orm_resources b, jsonb_array_elements(b.metadata->'file_metadata') AS file_metadata_again WHERE a.internal_resource='FileSet' AND a.updated_at > '2022-08-01' AND b.internal_resource='FileSet' AND b.updated_at > '2022-08-01' AND file_metadata @> '{"checksum": [{}]}' AND file_metadata_again @> '{"checksum": [{}]}' AND file_metadata->'checksum'->0->'md5' = file_metadata_again->'checksum'->0->'md5' AND a.id != b.id LIMIT 1;
```

Query:

```sql
select a.metadata->'cached_parent_id'->0->'id', a.id, b.id from orm_resources a, jsonb_array_elements(a.metadata->'file_metadata') AS file_metadata, orm_resources b, jsonb_array_elements(b.metadata->'file_metadata') AS file_metadata_again WHERE a.internal_resource='FileSet' AND a.updated_at > '2022-08-01' AND b.internal_resource='FileSet' AND b.updated_at > '2022-08-01' AND file_metadata @> '{"checksum": [{}]}' AND file_metadata_again @> '{"checksum": [{}]}' AND file_metadata->'checksum'->0->'md5' = file_metadata_again->'checksum'->0->'md5' AND a.id != b.id AND a.metadata->'cached_parent_id'->0->'id' = b.metadata->'cached_parent_id'->0->'id' GROUP BY a.metadata->'cached_parent_id'->0->'id', a.id, b.id;

```

Result: There are two. The previously found one, and https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/63567ec1-7d83-47de-b7f4-3f70913fa13a. I'll message Dan that he should redo that record.

comments.body:
Examples of urls that have come in with this error are:

* https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog?utf8=%E2%9C%93&f%5Baccess_facet%5D%5B0%5D=Online&f1=all_fields&f2=author&f3=title&op2=AND&op3=AND&q1=Tchaikovsky&q2&q3&range%5Bpub_date_start_sort%5D%5Bbegin%5D&range%5Bpub_date_start_sort%5D%5Bend%5D&search_field=advanced&sort=score+desc%2C+pub_date_start_sort+desc%2C+title_sort+asc&f_inclusive%5Bformat%5D%5B0%5D=Audio&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B0%5D=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B1%5D=elf1&commit=Search
* https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog?utf8=%E2%9C%93&f1=all_fields&f2=author&f3=title&op2=AND&op3=AND&q1=Cello+Suite+No.+3+in+C+Major%2C+BWV+1009&q2=bach&q3&range%5Bpub_date_start_sort%5D%5Bbegin%5D&range%5Bpub_date_start_sort%5D%5Bend%5D&search_field=advanced&sort=score+desc%2C+pub_date_start_sort+desc%2C+title_sort+asc&f_inclusive%5Bformat%5D%5B0%5D=Audio&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B0%5D=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B1%5D=Online&commit=Search

Note particularly the sections:
* `f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B0%5D=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B1%5D=elf1`
  * decoded: `f_inclusive[advanced_location_s][0]=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive[advanced_location_s][1]=elf1`
* `f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B0%5D=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive%5Badvanced_location_s%5D%5B1%5D=Online`
  * decoded: `f_inclusive[advanced_location_s][0]=Mendel+Music+Library&f_inclusive[advanced_location_s][1]=Online`

We don't know how these sections were built via the UI, but it's these constructions that are leading to getting a hash rather than a string or array.
